description: First Rughal, then Blackwolf show up at the 99 Steps Foundation, they come not bearing arms but rather, seeking assistance. Rughal seeks approval, claiming he's reformed his evil ways and is starting his own team of gem-bearers. Blackwolf brings his son whom he believes is a gem-bearer in need of assistance. Mystery and confusion rule the night amid rumors of a traitor among The 99.
name: The Return of Rughal

description: Is there a traitor in THE 99's headquarters? Dr. Ramzi is tricked into dispersing THE 99 into small teams around the world, leaving headquarters unprotected and open to attack by the nefarious Blackwolf and the Sphinx! Plus, the identity of the mysterious Sphinx is revealed!
name: The Sphinx Revealed!

description: When her world is turned upside down and she is stripped of everything she loves, Mercy must take on dark powers to help save the soul of her beloved Sarah.
name: Wolf & Raven

description: Mercy has tracked the cult of ravens to a coastal fishing village where they continue their rampage. The first wretched creature to be born of Karnstein's remains is unleashed!
name: Unleashed in the East

description: Mercy makes her way into the frozen mountains of the north. Along the way she meets strange new people, and finally faces off against the second creature born of the vampire lord.
name: Far, Far North

description: Detective Honeybear is an adorable bear detective in a noir, mystery world. Join him and his partner Detective Chance as they try to solve the case of the curious cap!
name: The Case of the Curious Cap

description: Detective Honeybear is the best -- and most adorable -- crime-solver around, but can even he crack the mystery of the terrible llamas? And in this issue: funnel cake! Not literally though, that would get messy.
name: The Mystery of the Terrible Llamas

description: Scrooge McDuck and Cousin Gladstone are up to no good. And as usual, that's bad news for Donald Duck. This time, the two schemers are planning to build a railroad?right through Donald's poor old house. The only problem? Donald doesn't want to move! So the two devise a nefarious scheme to frame Donald and have him arrested...leaving the house free to be torn down! They just forgot one thing -- Donald doesn't want to leave his home, and when Donald sets his mind to something, not even a prison island can stop him!

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Count of Monte Cristo

description: Donald Duck has escaped from the island prison where he was locked away, framed by Scrooge McDuck and Cousin Gladstone. And he escaped with a secret--a secret about a great treasure, told to him by a fellow prisoner. With it, Donald could finally have his revenge on the traitorous Scrooge and Gladstone. But instead of finding treasure or the shores of his home, Donald finds himself marooned on a desert island. All seems lost, and Donald seems doomed to spend years alone in this remote place -- but he might just find that things aren't always what they seem, and the solution could be right under his nose?

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Count of Monte Cristo

description: All for one and one for all! Donald Duck, Uncle Scrooge, Huey, Dewey and Louie are the King's musketeers! As they travel to Paris can Donald stay out of trouble and steer clear of the Beagle Boys?

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Three Musketeers

description: Donald Duck, Uncle Scrooge, Huey, Dewey and Louie are the King's musketeers. This adventure is inspired by a great classic... but Donald's always in trouble!

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Three Musketeers

description:
Super-scientist George Bakers newest invention, electronic retinal implants known as Cyber-Eyes, are nothing short of amazing. So amazing, in fact, and so cheap and easy to get, that some 40% of the population has gotten them within their first year on the market. But they arent perfect.

Far from it.

When things start going inexplicably and bizarrely wrong with the original test-subjects, George and his family will have to find out why before the problem spreads and causes world-wide panic.

Along the way theyll uncover ancient civilizations, corporate conspiracies, insane cults, other-dimensional creatures, awesome robots, subterranean cities, and Things Man Was Not Meant To Know.

Its going to be a wild ride.

Chapter 2: Wednesday

Deep beneath the Antarctic ice, archaeologist Emma Baker and her team have

spent over a year trying to unlock the secrets of an ancient alien city. As

the excavation pushes forwards, however, they'll learn that some secrets

can be deadly.
name: Wednesday

description:
Chapter 3: Wednesday... Again

While investigating the Cyber-Eyes malfunction, George, Hank, and

R.A.I.Ch.E.L. embark on a globe-trotting quest for answers. Meanwhile,

Abby and Varius dig through the shadier side of the Noreon corporation's

development practices.
name: Wednesday... Again

description: Set in a dystopian future, Danny finds himself in a quandary and Ron thinks he knows a good way out of a bad situation.
name: Drafted

description: Ron has something to answer for the morning after Danny's death while the 'powers that be' seize the opportunity to silence a threat.
name: Arrested

description: The debut of Tiger Lawyer features two original tales crossing multiple generes! In "Attorney at Rawr" our titular tiger defends an accused murder, leading to all out courtroom chaos! The series takes a turn for the noir in "Dead Cat Walking" as Tiger loses his first case, forcing him to take to the streets as he uncovers a plot much thicker than murder.

He's back! Tiger Lawyer #2 features two original stories from writer Ryan Ferrier: the courtroom riot "Dial P For Purr-der," with art from Matt McCray, and the continuing noir instalment "Bad Cat Rising," with art from Vic Malhotra and Adam Metcalfe. Tiger Lawyer #2 also features pin-ups from various up-and-coming comic artists.

Tomorrow Jones, 14 years-old and the second child in a family of superheroes. While she may be strong enough to fold an armored truck into origami, Tomorrow has to pretend to be a normal girl at school. Her father won't take her seriously, and her traditional heroine mother expects Tomorrow to follow in her footsteps. But Tomorrow doesn't want to dress in skimpy spandex though, and starts fighting crime unmasked and simply wearing jeans and a T-shirt with her real initials on it. All the while her parents keep trying to get her to do things "the traditional way" and Tomorrow finds she might be getting in over her head in the superhero community.

Tomorrow Jones, 14 years-old and the second child in a family of superheroes. After witnessing a bank robbery in progress in issue #1, Tomorrow used her incredible strength to intervene. Not wanting to hide her identity, Tomorrow reveals her name to the crowd of witnesses. However, her parents are none too happy about their daughter's public display of her powers. It looks like Tomorrow may be grounded indefinitely. That is until her mother Astraea's worst enemy Dementa comes tearing into town. Can Tomorrow prove she can fight crime her way, or is Dementa more of a challenge that she can handle?

description: Something is amuck at Turkey Grove Farms. Jasper's dad, the famous face of the farm's commercials, hasn't been seen since before Thanksgiving. Why is Jasper telling anyone who will listen of a great turkey uprising? Has Jasper gone crazy or is this another publicity stunt? One thing for is certain, business is booming and the turkey has never been more delicious. Everything evolves, why not turkeys?

The "Watering Hole Murders" investigation is underway and the fix is in! What is Jasper's real name and why does he hate it? What does Red keep in all the jars in the barn? Cover-ups, nosey-neighbors, a deeper look into turkey culture, and of course murder in the issue appropriately titled: "Death From Above."

Plain or peanut? Knowing the right answer can save your life. Schemes unfold, a jail break, a high speed police chase, and murder-- lots and lots of murder as Delia and the "Animal Freedom Movement" make their first appearance in this issue appropriately named: "Sooner Or Later, The Crazy Always Comes Out."

The first story arc, "The Fall," wraps up. Power plays and land grabs abound as schemes come to fruition. Oddly, nary a murder to be had, only love and betrayal --lots of lovin' and heaps of betrayal with a last page that raises the question: "Did they just go there?" Questions answered in this very special issue titled: "Love is in the Air."

volume.name: Mandy Picture Story Library For Girls
